label: TYPE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code to identify the kind of application.

label: ID
description: This field stores the ID you assign to the Application record when you create it.

label: SUBTYPE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code that identifies the application type.

label: FORMTYPE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code to identify the type of form used for the application.

label: EVENT
description: This field stores the number of the current application workflow event for the application.

label: EVENTDATE
description: This field stores the date the application workflow value in the Event Number field last changed.

label: CREATIONDATE
description: This field stores the current system date when you create the Application record.

label: EFFECTIVEDATE
description: This field stores the effective date of the Application record.

label: EXPIRATIONDATE
description: This field stores the date the Application record expires.

label: CLOSINGDATE
description: This field stores the date you close this Application record.

label: LASTFMDATE
description: This field stores the current system date whenever there is any file maintenance of an Application record or child record field.

label: RECORDCHANGEDATE
description: This field stores the system date in this field when you create, change, or save the Application record. Sometimes the system updates this field because the record was saved, even though there may not be any actual changes in the record.

label: SECONDAPPREQUEST
description: This field stores a description of a second application, if applicable.

label: SECONDAPPREQUESTAMT
description: This field stores the amount the member requests in a second application, if applicable.

label: SECONDAPPPAYMENT
description: This field stores the payment amount associated with the second application, if applicable.

label: THIRDAPPREQUEST
description: This field stores a description of a third application, if applicable.

label: THIRDAPPREQUESTAMT
description: This field stores the amount the member requests in a third application, if applicable.

label: THIRDAPPPAYMENT
description: This field stores the payment amount associated with the third application, if applicable.

label: CENSUSTRACT
description: This field stores the number of the census tract in which the applicant resides.

label: VIN
description: This field stores the vehicle identification number of any vehicle listed as collateral.

label: BRANCH
description: This field stores the number of the branch where the application originated.

label: CREDITBUREAU
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code to identify the credit bureau providing the credit report used to evaluate the application.

label: ACCOUNTTYPE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code to identify the type of account.

label: CREATEDBYUSER
description: This field stores the User ID and is populated when the record is created.

label: CREATEDATBRANCH
description: This field stores the branch ID of the branch where the Application record is created.

label: USERQUEUE
description: The field stores whose queue the application is residing in.

label: QUEUEPRIORITY
description: This field stores the level of importance given to this application.

label: QUEUEDATE
description: The field stores either the date the application was forwarded to the user or the date the last decision was assigned to the application.

label: QUEUETIME
description: The field stores either the time of day the application was forwarded to the user or the time of day the last decision was assigned to the application.

label: DECISIONCODE
description: This field stores a user number or a credit union-defined code to identify the person making the application decision.

label: DECISIONDATE
description: This field stores the date of the decision to approve, deny, or cancel the application, make a counter offer, or place the application in pending mode.

label: APPROVALCODE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code or the user number of the person who approved the application.

label: APPROVALDATE
description: This field stores the date the application was approved.

label: APPROVALAMOUNT
description: This field stores the approved loan amount.

label: APPLICATIONDATE
description: This field stores the current system date when you create the Application record.

label: CANCELLATIONDATE
description: This field stores the date you canceled the application.

label: PENDINGDATE
description: This field stores the date you place an application in pending mode to await further action.

label: PROCESSORCODE
description: This field stores the user number of the person who creates the application.

label: INFOREQUESTDATE
description: This field stores the most recent date you sent the applicant a notice of incomplete application or a request for information.

label: DENIALDATE
description: This field stores the date you denied the application.

label: DENIALREASON:1
description: These fields each store a credit union-defined code to indicate the reason for denying or canceling the application or for making a counter offer.

label: DENIALREASON:2
description: These fields each store a credit union-defined code to indicate the reason for denying or canceling the application or for making a counter offer.

label: DENIALREASON:3
description: These fields each store a credit union-defined code to indicate the reason for denying or canceling the application or for making a counter offer.

label: DENIALREASON:4
description: These fields each store a credit union-defined code to indicate the reason for denying or canceling the application or for making a counter offer.

label: DENIALREASON:5
description: These fields each store a credit union-defined code to indicate the reason for denying or canceling the application or for making a counter offer.

label: COUNTEREDORIGAMT
description: This field stores the original amount for which the member applied.

label: COUNTEROFFEREXPIREDATE
description: This field stores the date the counter offer expires.

label: LOANTYPE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code to identify the kind of loan the applicant is applying for.

label: EXISTINGLOANID
description: If the member is applying for an add-on to an existing loan, this field stores the ID of the existing Loan record.

label: EXISTINGLOANBALANCE
description: This field stores the balance of the loan specified at the Existing Loan ID field.

label: LOANCODE
description: This field stores a code that defines certain characteristics of the loan and determines how the system processes the loan.

label: BORROWDATE
description: This field stores the date you disburse funds for the loan.

label: FIRSTDUEDATE
description: This field stores the date the first loan payment is due.

label: PAYMENT
description: This field stores the amount of the loan payment.

label: LOANAMOUNT
description: This field stores the total amount of the loan.

label: TERMMONTHS
description: This field stores the number of months in the term of the loan.

label: MILITARYAPRLOAN
description: This field stores a code that indicates whether the loan qualifies for the military APR program.

label: LOANDESCRIPTION
description: This field stores a description of the loan.

label: LOANREFERENCE
description: This field stores any reference information about the loan.

label: ECOACODE
description: This field stores a code that indicates how the system populates the ECOA Code field in the Loan record if the loan is created automatically using the Loan Creation workflow action in Application Processing.

label: PURPOSECODE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code to indicate the purpose of the loan.

label: SECUREDCODE
description: This field stores a code that specifies the type of security, if any, for a loan.

label: COLLATERALCODE
description: This field stores a code that indicates the collateral offered for the loan.

label: COLLATERALDATE
description: This field stores the date the member offered the collateral for the loan.

label: CALLITEMSCHD
description: Primarily for users of the corporate interface: This field stores the numeric value of the set of Call/Put Item Schedules parameters used for call items.

label: CALLITEMSCHDTYPE
description: Formerly for users of the corporate interface: This field indicated whether the set of Call/Put Item Schedules parameters specified in the Call Item Schedule field is local or global.

label: PUTITEMSCHD
description: Primarily for users of the corporate interface: This field stores the numeric value of the set of Call/Put Item Schedules parameters used for put items.

label: PUTITEMSCHDTYPE
description: Primarily for users of the corporate interface: This field indicated whether the set of Call/Put Item Schedules parameters specified in the Put Item Schedule field is local or global.

label: AMORTIZATIONSCHD
description: Primarily for users of the corporate interface: This field stores the numeric value of the set of Amortization Schedules parameters.

label: AMORTIZATIONSCHDTYPE
description: Primarily for users of the corporate interface: This field indicates whether the set of Amortization Schedules parameters specified in the Amortization Schedule field is local or global.

label: INTERESTTYPE
description: This field stores a code that indicates the method for calculating loan interest that can be different for each Schedule record when using the MBS Multiple Repayment Programs Per Loan module.

label: INTERESTRATE
description: This field stores the interest rate of the loan.

label: PAYMENTTYPE
description: This field stores a code that indicates the method for calculating the payment.

label: PAYMENTCALCTYPE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code used for determining the calculation method for the loan.

label: PAYMENTMETHOD
description: This field stores a code that specifies the method of payment for a loan.

label: PAYMENTFREQUENCY
description: This field stores a code that specifies the frequency of loan payments.

label: DUEDATEADVANCECODE
description: This field stores a code that specifies how the system advances the due date when a payment is made to the loan.

label: MAXDUEDATEADVANCEPERIOD
description: This field stores the maximum number of periods the due date can be advanced into the future.

label: DUEDAY1
description: This field stores the day of the month on which the first payment is due for semimonthly loans, or the day of the month on which all payments are due for annual, semiannual, quarterly, bimonthly, or monthly loans.

label: DUEDAY2
description: This field stores the day of the month on which the second payment is due for semimonthly loans.

label: INITIALBCDSETTINGOPTION
description: This field stores a code that determines how the beginning cycle date will be set for non-billed loans and loans with a Loan record Payment Method of (2) Auto transfer.

label: DQCALCULATIONMETHOD
description: This field stores a code that defines the method used to calculate delinquency.

label: TRANSFERACCOUNTNUMBER
description: If loan payments are by automatic transfer of funds from another account, this field stores the number of the other account.

label: TRANSFERACCOUNTID
description: If loan payments are by automatic transfer of funds from another account, this field stores the ID of the Share record.

label: NOTEPURGEDATE
description: This field is currently unused.

label: PAYMENTSKIPS
description: This field stores the number of loan payments the member can skip.

label: PAYMENTSKIPSTARTDAY
description: This field stores a code that represents the due date of the first payment the member can skip.

label: BALLOONDATE
description: This field stores the date the balloon loan payment is due, if applicable.

label: BALLOONAMOUNT
description: This field stores the amount of a balloon payment, if applicable.

label: CREDITLIMIT
description: This field stores the credit limit for line-of-credit or credit card loans.

label: LIMITEXPIRATIONDATE
description: This field stores the expiration date of the loan's credit limit.

label: LOANMATURITYDATE
description: This field stores the date the loan matures.

label: LOANTOVALUERATIO
description: This field contains the loan to value ratio (the ratio of the loan amount to the appraised home value).

label: APPRAISEDAMOUNT
description: This field stores the appraised amount of the collateral for the loan.

label: APPRAISALOFFSET
description: This field stores the offset value of the collateral for a second trust deed loan.

label: ESCROWAMOUNT
description: This field stores the amount of the payment to post to the share identified by the value in the Escrow ID field.

label: ESCROWID
description: This field stores the ID of the Share record to which the system should post the escrow amount whenever a member makes a loan payment.

label: UNAMORTIZEDFEES
description: This field stores the total amount of fees to be amortized over the loan term, according to FASB 91.

label: PREPAIDFINANCECHG
description: This field stores additional amounts, that can be included in a loan.

label: ORIGINALRATE
description: This field stores the original effective Annual Percentage Rate.

label: RISKRATE
description: This field stores a value that increases the calculated margin rate when the Rate Change Processing batch program calculates the new interest rate for non-credit card loans tied to an interest rate index.

label: DISCOUNTRATE
description: This field stores a value that decreases the calculated margin rate when the Rate Change Processing batch program calculates the new interest rate for non-credit card loans tied to an interest rate index.

label: EFFECTIVEAPR
description: This field stores the current effective Annual Percentage Rate.

label: APR
description: This field stores the Annual Percentage Rate.

label: FASB91CODE
description: This field stores the FASB 91 code used with loan type codes to create combinations that post to designated General Ledger accounts.

label: INSURANCETYPE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code that indicates whether the member has elected to purchase insurance.

label: INSURANCEMAX
description: This field stores the maximum insurable balance for the insurance type selected.

label: SINGLEPREMIUMLIFE
description: This field stores the calculated amount of single premium life insurance.

label: SINGLEPREMIUMDISABILITY
description: This field stores the calculated amount of single premium disability insurance.

label: FIRSTINSBIRTHDATE
description: This field stores the first insurer's date of birth.

label: SECONDINSBIRTHDATE
description: This field stores the second insurer's date of birth.

label: INSURABILITYCODE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code that indicates whether the loan applicant can be insured.

label: INSURANCE1CHOSEN
description: This field stores a code that indicates if the applicant has elected to purchase single credit life insurance.

label: INSURANCE2CHOSEN
description: This field stores a code that indicates if the applicant has elected to purchase joint credit life insurance.

label: INSURANCE3CHOSEN
description: This field stores a code that indicates if the applicant has elected to purchase credit disability insurance.

label: OVLOPTIN
description: This field stores a code that indicates if the credit union prints the revocation statement.

label: OVLAUTHFEE
description: This field stores a code that indicates whether to authorize or assess a fee for credit card over-the-limit transactions.

label: CUTOTALSACCTNUMBER:1
description: These fields each store the account number of another account to be included in the credit union totals.

label: CUTOTALSACCTNUMBER:2
description: These fields each store the account number of another account to be included in the credit union totals.

label: CUTOTALSACCTNUMBER:3
description: These fields each store the account number of another account to be included in the credit union totals.

label: CUTOTALSACCTNUMBER:4
description: These fields each store the account number of another account to be included in the credit union totals.

label: CUTOTALSACCTNUMBER:5
description: These fields each store the account number of another account to be included in the credit union totals.

label: ORIGRISKGRADE
description: This field stores the original risk grade assigned to the note when it was originated.

label: CREDITSCORETYPE
description: This field stores a credit union-defined code to specify the type of credit score to be calculated for the application.

label: CREDITSCORE
description: This field stores the results of Symitar programmed credit score calculations.

label: BUREAUSCORE:1
description: This field stores the most recent credit score from the Experian credit bureau for the main applicant for the loan.

label: BUREAUSCORE:2
description: This field stores the most recent credit score from the Equifax credit bureau for the main applicant for the loan.

label: BUREAUSCORE:3
description: This field stores the most recent credit score from the TransUnionÂ® credit bureau for the main applicant for the loan.

label: CUTOTALOPENENDLOANS
description: This field stores the sum of all loan balances in Loan records in the member's account with a value in the Loan Code field of (1) Open End, a blank in the Close Date field, and a blank in the Charge-off Date field.

label: CUTOTALCLOSEDENDLOANS
description: This field stores the sum of all loan balances in Loan records in the member's account with a value in the Loan Code field of (0) Closed End, a blank in the Close Date field, and a blank in the Charge-off Date field.

label: CUTOTALLOCLOANS
description: This field stores the sum of all loan balances in Loan records in the member's account with a value in the Loan Code field of (2) Line of Credit, a blank in the Close Date field, and a blank in the Charge-off Date field.

label: CUTOTALCREDITCARDLOANS
description: This field stores the sum of all loan balances, unpaid interest, and unpaid late charges in Loan records in the member's account with a value in the Loan Code field of (3) Credit Card, a blank in the Close Date field, and a blank in the Charge-off Date field.

label: CUTOTALCREDITLIMIT
description: This field stores the sum of all credit limits in all Loan records in the member's account with a blank in the Close Date field, and a blank in the Charge-off Date field.

label: CUTOTALOPENENDPAYMENTS
description: This field stores the sum of all standard payments for all Loan records in the member's account with a value in the Loan Code field of (1) Open End, a blank in the Close Date field, and a blank in the Charge-off Date field.

label: CUTOTALCLOSEDENDPAYMENTS
description: This field stores the sum of all standard payments for all Loan records in the member's account with a value in the Loan Code field of (0) Closed End, a blank in the Close Date field, and a blank in the Charge-off Date field.

label: CUTOTALLOCPAYMENTS
description: This field stores the sum of all standard payments for all Loan records in the member's account with a value in the Loan Code field of (2) Line of Credit, a blank in the Close Date field, and a blank in the Charge-off Date field.

label: CUTOTALCREDCARDPAYMENTS
description: This field stores the sum of all standard payments for all Loan records in the member's account with a value in the Loan Code field of (3) Credit Card, a blank in the Close Date field, and a blank in the Charge-off Date field.

label: CUTOTALSHARES
description: This field stores the sum of all available balances in Share records in the member's account with a value in the Share Code field of (0) Share and a value in the IRS Code field of (0) Normal.

label: CUTOTALDRAFTS
description: This field stores the sum of all available balances in Share records in the member's account with a value in the Share Code field of (1) Draft and a value in the IRS Code field of (0) Normal.

label: CUTOTALCERTIRAS
description: This field stores the sum of all available balances in Share records in the member's account with a value in the Share Code field of (2) Certificate or (3) Club, or any share with a non-zero value in the IRS Code field.

label: DEBTRATIOTYPE:1
description: These fields each store a credit union-defined code to specify a debt ratio calculation based on the definition of that Debt Ratio Type field.

label: DEBTRATIOTYPE:2
description: These fields each store a credit union-defined code to specify a debt ratio calculation based on the definition of that Debt Ratio Type field.

label: DEBTRATIOTYPE:3
description: These fields each store a credit union-defined code to specify a debt ratio calculation based on the definition of that Debt Ratio Type field.

label: DEBTRATIOTYPE:4
description: These fields each store a credit union-defined code to specify a debt ratio calculation based on the definition of that Debt Ratio Type field.

label: DEBTRATIOTYPE:5
description: These fields each store a credit union-defined code to specify a debt ratio calculation based on the definition of that Debt Ratio Type field.

label: DEBTRATIO:1
description: These fields each store a debt ratio calculated according to the credit union-defined debt ratio type in that Debt Ratio Type field.

label: DEBTRATIO:2
description: These fields each store a debt ratio calculated according to the credit union-defined debt ratio type in that Debt Ratio Type field.

label: DEBTRATIO:3
description: These fields each store a debt ratio calculated according to the credit union-defined debt ratio type in that Debt Ratio Type field.

label: DEBTRATIO:4
description: These fields each store a debt ratio calculated according to the credit union-defined debt ratio type in that Debt Ratio Type field.

label: DEBTRATIO:5
description: These fields each store a debt ratio calculated according to the credit union-defined debt ratio type in that Debt Ratio Type field.

label: INDIRECTDEALERNUM
description: If the Dealer Reserve Accounting module has been implemented, this field stores the indirect dealer number.

label: TOTALINCOME
description: This field stores the combined total of the values in the Curr Gross Mo Pay fields in all Person records under the Application record and the values in the Monthly Income fields in all Finance records under the Application record.

label: TOTALEXPENSES
description: This field stores the combined total of the values in the CU Open End Pmts, CU Closed End Pmts, CU LOC Pmts, CU Credit Card Pmts, and payment fields in the Application record and the values in the Monthly Expense fields in all Finance records under the Application record.

label: TOTALASSETS
description: This field stores the combined total of the values in the CU Share Bal, CU Draft Bal, and CU Cert IRA Bal fields in the Application record and the values in the Asset Value fields in all Finance records under the Application record.

label: TOTALLIABILITIES
description: This field stores the combined total of the values in the CU Opn End Loan Bal, CU Cls End Loan Bal, CU LOC Loan Bal, CU Cred Card Ln Bal, and Loan Amount fields in the Application record and the values in the Liability Balance fields in all Finance records under the Application record.

label: TOTALCREDITLIMITS
description: This field stores the combined total of the value in the CU Total Credit Lim field in the Application record and the values in the Credit Limit fields in all Finance records under the Application record.

label: INDIRECTPLANID
description: If the Dealer Reserve Accounting module has been implemented, this field stores the reserve plan ID associated with this indirect loan.

label: GROSSMONTHLYPAY1
description: This field stores the amount of the person's current monthly gross pay from the Curr Gross MO Pay field from the first Person record (record 00) under the Application record.

label: NETMONTHLYPAY1
description: This field stores the amount of this person's current monthly net pay from the Curr Net MO Pay field from the first Person record (record 00) under the Application record.

label: GROSSMONTHLYPAY2
description: This field stores the amount of the person's current monthly gross pay from the Curr Gross MO Pay field from the second Person record (record 00) under the Application record.

label: NETMONTHLYPAY2
description: This field stores the amount of this person's current monthly net pay from the Curr Net MO Pay field from the second Person record (record 00) under the Application record.

label: CBILOCATOR:1
description: These fields each store a unique credit bureau information (CBI) request identifier for that request.

label: CBILOCATOR:2
description: These fields each store a unique credit bureau information (CBI) request identifier for that request.

label: CBILOCATOR:3
description: These fields each store a unique credit bureau information (CBI) request identifier for that request.

label: CBILOCATOR:4
description: These fields each store a unique credit bureau information (CBI) request identifier for that request.

label: CBILOCATOR:5
description: These fields each store a unique credit bureau information (CBI) request identifier for that request.

label: CBILOCATOR:6
description: These fields each store a unique credit bureau information (CBI) request identifier for that request.

label: PREFLOCATOR
description: This field stores the system-defined locator number from the associated Preference record's Locator field.

label: INDIRECTPLANID
description: If the Dealer Reserve Accounting module has been implemented, this field stores the reserve plan ID associated with this indirect loan.

label: PROPERTYADDRESSTYPE
description: This field stores a code that indicates how the system stores the property address information that secures a mortgage loan.

label: PROPERTYJURISDICTION
description: This field stores the property's jurisdiction (county and state).

label: ASSESSORPARCELNUMBER
description: This field stores the property's Assessor Parcel Number or Numbers (APN).

label: MTGNUMPROP
description: This field stores the number of properties that secure this mortgage loan.

label: PMIORIGINALVALUE
description: This field stores the original value of the collateral for the loan.

label: PMIPURCHASEPRICE
description: This field stores the purchase price or sales price of the property securing the mortgage, as reflected in the purchase contract.

label: PMIAPPRAISEDVALUE
description: This field stores the value at the time the subject residential mortgage transaction was completed.

label: PMILTVRATIO
description: This field contains the loan amount divided by the lesser of the value in the Purchase Price field or the value in the PMI Appraised Value field at the time of loan completion.

label: HIGHRISKCODE
description: This field stores a code that specifies whether a loan is considered high risk.

label: COMBOLNSEGMENTMAX
description: This field stores a value to identify the maximum number of segments (including Segment 0) that can be added to a combination loan.

label: COMBOPMTORDERMETH
description: This field stores a code that determines the order to pay segments for SymChoice Loans.

label: COMBOSEG0PMTORDER
description: This field stores a code that determines the order to set Segment 0 when used with the Combo Payment Order Method field for SymChoice Loans.

label: NEWSEGCUTOFFOPTION
description: This field stores a code that controls how the system calculates the Due Date field in the projections screen of a Segment record.

label: NEWSEGCUTOFFDAYS
description: This field stores the number of days to add to the Loan Date field in the projections screen to calculate the segment cutoff date.

label: SEG0DESCRIPTION
description: This field stores the description of the segment for SymChoice Loans.

label: SEG0PAYMENTORDER
description: This field stores a code that indicates the order in which Segment 0 will be paid for a Loan Payment (LP) transaction.

label: SEG0PAYMENT
description: This field contains the payment for Segment 0 for a SymChoice Loan.

label: CAPERCENT
description: This field stores the percentage of the overall credit limit that can be allocated to cash advances.

label: CALIMITMAX
description: This field stores the maximum amount that can be allocated to cash advances from the overall credit limit.

label: BTPERCENT
description: This field stores the percentage of the overall credit limit that can be allocated to balance transfers.

label: BTLIMITMAX
description: This field stores the maximum amount that can be allocated to balance transfers from the overall credit limit.

label: COMBINEDCABTPERCENT
description: This field stores the percentage of the overall credit limit to be allocated to cash advances and balance transfers combined.

label: COMBINEDCABTLIMITMAX
description: This field stores the maximum amount that can be allocated to cash advances and balance transfers from the overall credit limit.

label: HMDAUNIVERSALLOANIDENTIFIER1
description: This field stores the unique identifier of the covered loan or application.

label: HMDAUNIVERSALLOANIDENTIFIER2
description: This field stores up to five additional Universal Loan Identifier (ULI) characters if the ULI was previously established outside of the system.

label: HMDALOANTYPE
description: This field stores a code that indicates the type of covered loan or application.

label: HMDALOANPURPOSE
description: This field stores a code that indicates the purpose of the covered loan or application.

label: HMDAPREAPPROVAL
description: This field stores a code that indicates whether the covered loan or application involved a request for a preapproval of a home purchase loan under a preapproval program.

label: HMDACONSTRUCTIONMETHOD
description: This field stores a code that indicates the construction method for the dwelling.

label: HMDAOCCUPANCYTYPE
description: This field stores a code that indicates the occupancy type of the residence.

label: HMDAACTIONTAKEN
description: This field stores a code that indicates the action taken on the covered loan or application.

label: HMDAACTIONTAKENDATE
description: This field stores the date of action taken.

label: HMDAPROPERTYSTREETADDRESS
description: This field stores the street address of the property.

label: HMDAPROPERTYCITY
description: This field stores the city of the property.

label: HMDAPROPERTYSTATE
description: This field stores the two-letter state code of the property.

label: HMDAPROPERTYZIPCODE
description: This field stores the ZIP Code of the property.

label: HMDAPROPERTYCOUNTY
description: This field stores the Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) numerical code for the county.

label: HMDACENSUSTRACT
description: This field stores the Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) numerical code and the census tract number as defined by the U.S. Census Bureau.

label: HMDAANNUALINCOME
description: This field stores the gross annual income (in dollars) used in making the credit decision.

label: HMDAPURCHASERTYPE
description: This field stores a code that indicates the type of entity purchasing a covered loan from your institution.

label: HMDARATESPREAD
description: This field stores the difference between the covered loan's annual percentage rate (APR) and the average prime offer rate (APOR) for a comparable transaction.

label: HMDARATESPREADSIGN
description: This field stores a code that specifies a positive or negative for the value in the Rate Spread field.

label: HMDAHOEPASTATUS
description: This field stores a code that indicates whether to report the status of the covered loan for the Home Ownership and Equity Protection Act (HOEPA) as a high-cost mortgage.

label: HMDALIENSTATUS
description: This field stores a code that indicates the lien status of the property securing the covered loan.

label: HMDADENIALREASONOTHER:2
description: These fields store text that defines the HMDA denial reason referred to when any of the Denial Reason 1â4 fields are set to (9) Other.

label: HMDADENIALREASONOTHER:3
description: These fields store text that defines the HMDA denial reason referred to when any of the Denial Reason 1â4 fields are set to (9) Other.

label: HMDADENIALREASONOTHER:4
description: These fields store text that defines the HMDA denial reason referred to when any of the Denial Reason 1â4 fields are set to (9) Other.

label: HMDADENIALREASONOTHER:5
description: These fields store text that defines the HMDA denial reason referred to when any of the Denial Reason 1â4 fields are set to (9) Other.

label: HMDADENIALREASONOTHER:6
description: These fields store text that defines the HMDA denial reason referred to when any of the Denial Reason 1â4 fields are set to (9) Other.

label: HMDADENIALREASONOTHER:7

label: HMDATOTALLOANCOSTS
description: This field stores the total loan costs amount.

label: HMDATOTALPOINTSFEES
description: This field stores the total points and fees charged with the covered loan.

label: HMDAORIGINATIONCHARGES
description: This field stores the total of all itemized amounts that are designated borrower-paid at or before closing.

label: HMDANEGAMORTIND

label: HMDAOTHERNONAMORTFEATURES

label: HMDAMULTIFAMILYAFFORDUNITS

label: DEALERCODE
description: This field stores the dealer code for a lease loan.

label: DEALERRESERVE
description: This field stores the amount of the dealer reserve for a lease loan.

label: SALESTAXRATE
description: This field contains the current lease loan sales tax rate at the time of the inquiry.

label: SALESTAXSTATEINDICATOR
description: This field stores a code that determines how state sales tax will be used as part of the information required to compute the sales tax.

label: SALESTAXCOUNTYINDICATOR
description: This field stores a code that determines how county sales tax will be used as part of the information required to compute the sales tax.

label: SALESTAXCITYINDICATOR
description: This field stores a code that determines how city sales tax will be used as part of the information required to compute the sales tax.

label: LESSEESTATE
description: This field stores the two-character state code where the car is registered as part of the information required to compute the sales tax.

label: LESSEECOUNTY
description: This field stores the county where the car is registered as part of the information required to compute the sales tax.

label: LESSEECITY
description: This field stores the city where the car is registered as part of the information required to compute the sales tax.

label: FIXEDLESSEESTATETAXRATE
description: This field stores a fixed state sales tax rate for the lessee state.

label: FIXEDLESSEECOUNTYTAXRATE
description: This field stores a fixed county sales tax rate for the lessee county.

label: FIXEDLESSEECITYTAXRATE
description: This field stores a fixed city sales tax rate for the lessee city.

label: LEASETERMINATEDATE
description: This field stores the date when the member terminates a lease loan by surrendering the vehicle.

label: LEASETERMINATEFEE
description: This field stores the fee amount to be charged for a loan paid off before the balloon date.

label: LEASEDISPOSITIONDATE
description: This field stores the date when the disposition fee is charged when a vehicle is turned back in at the end of a lease.

label: LEASEDISPOSITIONFEE
description: This field stores the fee amount to be charged when a vehicle is turned back in at the end of a lease.

label: STATESALESTAXRATE
description: This field contains the current lease loan state sales tax at the time of the inquiry.

label: CNTYSALESTAXRATE
description: This field contains the current lease loan county sales tax at the time of the inquiry.

label: CITYSALESTAXRATE
description: This field contains the current lease loan city sales tax at the time of the inquiry.

label: DEALERSTATE
description: This field stores the two-character state code where the car was leased as part of the information required to compute the sales tax.

label: DEALERCOUNTY
description: This field stores the county where the car was leased as part of the information required to compute the sales tax.

label: DEALERCITY
description: This field stores the city where the car was leased as part of the information required to compute the sales tax.

label: FIXEDDEALERSTATETAXRATE
description: This field stores a fixed state sales tax rate for the dealer state.

label: FIXEDDEALERCOUNTYTAXRATE
description: This field stores a fixed county sales tax rate for the dealer county.

label: FIXEDDEALERCITYTAXRATE
description: This field stores a fixed city sales tax rate for the dealer city.
